  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1983-06-16", 
    "text": "Amends the Internal Revenue Code to provide a refundable income tax credit equal to 15 percent of the purchase price of a security device placed in a building or residence. Allows a maximum credit of $400. Includes as security devices eligible for such credit locks, fire, smoke, temperature, gas, anti-theft, anti-intrusion, and personal health emergency alarms. Excludes bars, screens and other physical barriers."
